{#-
  apm.yml — MANAGED (re-rendered byte-identically at reproduce, Q3).

  Renders the APM dependency layer for the generated project from the injected
  `apm_packages` list. Mirrors the schema of the bailiff repo's own /apm.yml
  (name / version / description / target / dependencies.apm[]) and the shape
  `apm init` produces.

  Sources (FR-002a): APM has no separate consumer "catalogue/registry" block in
  a project apm.yml — each dependency locator carries its own source inline
  (`owner/repo/packages/name#constraint`), exactly like the bailiff repo's apm.yml.
  So "configure >= 1 source" is satisfied by having >= 1 dependency locator (each
  IS a source). The empty set is refused before this file renders (Q4 /
  apm_packages validator), so `dependencies.apm` is always non-empty here.

  The install task (uvx --from apm-cli==<ver> apm install) resolves these and
  writes apm.lock.yaml as external state (NOT rendered here, NOT byte-guaranteed).
-#}
name: {{ project_name | default('project', true) }}
version: 0.1.0
description: {{ description | default('APM dependency layer for ' ~ (project_name | default('project', true)), true) }}
# Which agent platforms to deploy to. Claude + Codex is bailiff's own default
# target pair; adjust to your project's runtimes.
target: claude,codex
includes: auto

dependencies:
  apm:
{%- for pkg in apm_packages %}
    - {{ pkg }}
{%- endfor %}
